// regardless of which promise completes first. This is different from Promise.all(), which waits for *all* promises to complete 
// (or reject) before proceeding. 

// For example, imagine you are fetching data from multiple APIs to determine which one has the fastest response time. 
// You could use Promise.race() to select the API that returns data the quickest, even if one API is significantly faster than others. 
